3. collapse(2) is used to prevent race conditions between threads.  
4. It allows two threads to work on the same row of the matrix at the same time.  
5. It is used to reduce memory consumption during parallel matrix addition.

25\. In a parallel merge sort implementation, how does the divide and conquer strategy improve the efficiency of sorting large datasets?

3. **It divides the problem recursively, solves smaller subproblems in parallel, and then combines the solutions, resulting in improved load balancing and reduced total execution time.**  
4. Divide and conquer improves memory usage by splitting the dataset into several small arrays.  
5. It converts a serial sort into a bubble sort.
